{"title":"Make at suggest uncommitted changes","tags":["open"],"date":"2009-11-17T17:32:47Z","author":"Simon Chiang <simon.chiang@pinnacol.com>","type":"issue","content":"If you fix an issue and then try to update the issue before committing the changes, the 'at' field should suggest that you commit you changes first.  This will help prevent circumstances where at points to a commit prior to where it is actually solved.","at":"1861a333cd08830c13e6b7a3f74ba54fe6bdb606","state":"open"}